issue_body:
When generating XML using a JTOX driver generated from a yang model the constraints on leaves are not checked (only the type).

e.g. For the following yang model 

~~~
module jtox-test
{
   prefix jt;
   
   namespace "urn:jt";

   container jtox-test {
      leaf host {
         description
         "The hostname of the server";
         type string {
            pattern '[.0-9A-Za-z_\-]*' {
               error-message "Must contain only letters, numbers, underscores or dashes";
            }
            length "1..64";
         }
         mandatory true;
      }
      leaf constrained-parameter {
         description
         "A uint8 constrained to the values 1-10";
         type uint8 {
            range "1..10" {
               error-message "Invalid value for attribute 'constrained-parameter'. Valid values are in range:[1,10]";
            }
         }
      }
   }
}
~~~
And using the below as input to json2xml
~~~
{
    "jtox-test:jtox-test": {
        "constrained-parameter": 99,
        "host": "abc"
    }
}
~~~
The following XML is generated.
~~~
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<nc:config xmlns:jt="urn:jt" xmlns:nc="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:netconf:base:1.0">
  <jt:jtox-test>
    <jt:host>abc</jt:host>
    <jt:constrained-parameter>99</jt:constrained-parameter>
  </jt:jtox-test>
</nc:config>
~~~
This doesn't conform to the yang model (constrained-parameter is only allowed to be in the range [1:10].

Should/can this checking be done in json2xml or should all output of json2xml be validated with yang2dsdl (using -v)?

